btrplace.solver.choco

Interface MisplacedVMsEstimator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ChocoConstraint, CObjective
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CAmong, CBan, CFence, CGather, CKilled, CLonely, CMaxOnline, CMinMTTR, COffline, COnline, COverbook, CPreserve, CQuarantine, CReady, CResourceCapacity, CRoot, CRunning, CRunningCapacity, CSequentialVMTransitions, CSleeping, CSplit, CSplitAmong, CSpread

    public interface MisplacedVMsEstimator
    An interface to specify an object that can estimated a supposed set of misplaced VMs in a model.

    This information will be used by the ChocoReconfigurationAlgorithm to restrict the amount of VMs to consider in the reconfiguration algorithm to a minimum.

    The set of mis-placed VMs is not necessarily optimal but it must be good enough to be able to compute a solution by only managing these VMs.

    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier
